{"lemma":"دُبْرَيْ","slug":"دُبْرَيْ","root":"د.ب.ر","root_slug":"د-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"دُبْر","root":"دبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":18},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":9,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12004","n12005","n12006","n12007"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be hindmost, to come behind, to follow"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn the back"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to elapse, to pass (of time)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow old, to age"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to veer to the west"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be turned backwards"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fall behind the aim"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take away"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have galls in the back, to have sores in the back"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to arrange, to dispose, to plan, to prepare, to organize, to hatch, to contrive, to devise, to forecast","examples":[{"text":"يُدَبِّرُ الْأَمْرَ مِنَ السَّمَاءِ إِلَى الْأَرْضِ ثُمَّ يَعْرُجُ إِلَيْهِ فِي يَوْمٍ كَانَ مِقْدَارُهُ أَلْفَ سَنَةٍ مِّمَّا تَعُدُّونَ","english":"He arranges [each] matter from the heaven to the earth; then it will ascend to Him in a Day, the extent of which is a thousand years of those which you count."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set free"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to direct, to manage, to regulate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَبَرَ (dabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَبِرَ (dabira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"back, back side, reverse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"buttocks"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anus"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rear part"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"end, tail"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"swarm, flock, drove"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"great wealth, much property"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"having galls in the back"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Afroasiatic *dâb-. Compare دُبْر (dubr, “back”), perhaps cognate with Hebrew דִּבֵּר (“to speak”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12004","headword_ar":"دَبَرَى","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12005","headword_ar":"دَبْرِىٌّ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12006","headword_ar":"دَبَرِىٌّ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Backward:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"late"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEilomu qabaliY~Nwalayosa biAld~abariY~i","text_ar":"العِلْمُ قَبَلِىٌّوَلَيْسَ بِالدَّبَرِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [True"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"learning is prompt, and is not backward"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., the man of sound learning answers thee quickly; but the backward says, I must consider it. (Th, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiEotu SaAHibiY dabariy~FA","text_ar":"تَبِعْتُ صَاحِبِى دَبَرِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I followed my companion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"fearing that he would escape me, after having been with him, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having fallen back from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~u Alr~aA^oYi Ald~abariY~u","text_ar":"شَرُّ الرَّاْىِ الدَّبَرِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, K *) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The worst opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsel, is that which occurs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"late, when the want"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is past;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K, * TA;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the affair is past:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabariY~N","text_ar":"دَبَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"signifies an opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a counsel, not deeply looked into;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAbN","text_ar":"جَوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an answer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a reply."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN laA yuSal~iY","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ لَا يُصَلِّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApa A_il~aA dabariy~FA","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةَ اـِلَّا دَبَرِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, M, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daboriy~FA","text_ar":"دَبْرِيًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, K,) and the relaters of traditions say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duburiy~FA","text_ar":"دُبُرِيًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which is said in the K to be a corruption, but it may have been heard from a good authority, and with respect to the rules of the language is chaste, for, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabariY~N","text_ar":"دَبَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a rel. n. irregularly formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duburN","text_ar":"دُبُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one performs not prayer save in the last part of its time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, K *) It is said in"},{"kind":"page_break","n":847},{"kind":"text","text":"a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaA^otiY AlS~alaApi A_il~aA dabariy~FA","text_ar":"لَا يَاْتِى الصَّلَاةِ اـِلَّا دَبَرِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in another, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~A duborFA","text_ar":"الّا دُبْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daborFA","text_ar":"دَبْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different relations; (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will not come to prayer save at the last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"late:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in another, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataY AlS~alaApa dibaArFA","text_ar":"اَتَى الصَّلَاةَ دِبَارًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came to prayer at the latest of the times thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after the time had gone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibaArN","text_ar":"دِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duburN","text_ar":"دُبُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duborN","text_ar":"دُبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last of the times"},{"kind":"text","text":"of prayer &c. (IAar, TA.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a fulaAnN daboriy~FA","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ فُلَانٌ دَبْرِيًّا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"latest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbry~FA","text_ar":"دبريًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the accus. case as an adv. n. of time [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duborFA","text_ar":"دُبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daborFA","text_ar":"دَبْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibaArFA","text_ar":"دِبَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or as a denotative of state with respect to the agent of the verb. (TA.) In the passage in the K [where it is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabariY~N","text_ar":"دَبَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer in the last of its time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], there is a looseness. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["AZ","S","M","A","K","AHeyth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n12007","headword_ar":"دُبُرِىٌّ","root":"dbx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}